	dprr:hasNoteText "Quaestor or Proquaestor 48. The man who buried Pompey the Great in Egypt (Auct. Vir. Ill. 77. 12, Servius Cordus; Lucan 8.715-717, . . . Cordus. / Quaestor ab Icario Cinyreae litore Cypri / infaustus Magni fuerat comes.). (RS, MS-RP 1.288-289)\n" ;
